    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-30T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-30T06:00:00-05:00" n="735"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24 FLC/12–3047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-30T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 30, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1585. On Dec 29 OFLC authorized its Shanghai rep by cable (1) to transfer under
                    Nov 6 contract with ChiGovt nondemilitarized combat material declared by owning
                    agency specifically for 8⅓ Group Program, and (2) to sell to China ammunition
                    and explosives (whether allocated under 8⅓ Program or otherwise) declared
                    surplus by owning agency at nominal charge of one percent of procurement cost.
                    On completion contract arrangements Chinese will be free to take delivery via
                    any transportation facilities available to them.</p>
                <p>Minister-Counselor should inform FonMin in sense of above, indicating that
                    contract can be concluded before end of year.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
